# Aperture Configuration
# Copy to .env and customize as needed

# =============================================================================
# PROXY SETTINGS
# =============================================================================

# Port for Aperture proxy (default: 5400)
# APERTURE_PORT=5400

# Log level: error, warn, info, debug, trace (default: info)
# RUST_LOG=info,aperture_lib=debug

# =============================================================================
# TESTING ONLY (optional)
# =============================================================================
# These are NOT required for normal use. Aperture is a transparent proxy —
# it forwards the API keys that your tools (Claude Code, Codex, etc.) already have.
#
# Only set these if you want to test the proxy directly with curl.

# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# =============================================================================
# USAGE
# =============================================================================
# Aperture sits between your AI tools and their APIs. To use:
#
# 1. Start Aperture (pnpm tauri dev or the built app)
# 2. Point your tool at the proxy:
#
#    # Claude Code
#    ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5400 claude
#
#    # Codex CLI
#    OPENAI_API_BASE=http://localhost:5400 codex
#
#    # Any OpenAI-compatible tool
#    OPENAI_BASE_URL=http://localhost:5400 your-tool
#
# The tool's existing API key flows through — Aperture just observes and forwards.
